      "type": "text",
      "title": "The Main Event \ud83c\udfaa",
      "content": "Every Dart program starts with a `main()` function.\n\nThink of it as the **front door** to your code. If `main()` isn't there, Dart doesn't know where to start!"
    },
    {
      "id": "s_ch1_l2_2",
      "type": "code",
      "title": "Your First Code",
      "content": "Here is what `main()` looks like. We use `print()` to talk to the screen:",
      "codeSnippet": "void main() {\n  print('Hello, World!');\n}",
      "codeLanguage": "dart",
      "canRunCode": true
